{{Quote|Perhaps I'll occupy the ninety-nine percent of my cognitive module ''not'' engaged by my chores by solving Chun's Theory of Reductional Infinity.|Protocol droid I-5YQ|<ref name="MedStar I">''[[MedStar I: Battle Surgeons]]''</ref>}}
'''Chun''' was an individual who formulated [[Chun's Theory of Reductional Infinity]]. The theory had not been solved<ref name="MedStar I" /> by [[20 BBY/Legends|20 BBY]].<ref name="TERC">''[[The Essential Reader's Companion]]'' dates the events of ''[[MedStar I: Battle Surgeons]]'' to [[20 BBY/Legends|20 BBY]].</ref> During that [[Standard year/Legends|year]], the underemployed [[5YQ-series protocol droid|protocol droid]] [[I-5YQ]] considered using the free space of his [[Droid brain/Legends|cognitive module]] in solving the formula.<ref name="MedStar I" />

==Behind the scenes==
Chun was first mentioned in ''[[MedStar I: Battle Surgeons]]'', the first novel of the [[MedStar Duology]]. ''Battle Surgeons'' was written by [[Steve Perry]] and [[Michael Reaves]], and published in [[2004]].<ref name="MedStar I" />

